{
  "texts": [
    "Glutamine is an important metabolic fuel that helps meet the high demand for energy, biosynthetic precursors, and reducing agents in rapidly proliferating cancer cells (71).",
    "In Figure 2, glutamine is transported to the cytoplasm through the solute carrier family 1, member 5 (SLC1A5) (72), and is converted to glutamate in the mitochondria through a deamination reaction catalyzed by glutaminase.",
    "Glutamate is converted to the TCA cycle intermediate a-ketoglutarate (a-KG) by glutamate dehydrogenase (73).",
    "a-KG is a critical metabolite that serves in both ATP production and in replenishing TCA cycle intermediates (74).",
    "Glutamine metabolism is essential for developing effector T cells (75)."
  ]
}